The paper proposes a new data structure for approximate nearest neighbor search, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed approach involves graph traversal, which is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the approach on large scale datasets, which is a common theme in database systems (cs.DB).
